cs.NI, cs.DC, cs.IT, cs.SI, cs.PF 

The paper discusses scheduling algorithms for hybrid switching in data centers, which involves both networking and distributed computing. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also deals with data center architecture and optimization, which falls under cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The paper uses submodular optimization techniques, which are commonly used in cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Finally, the paper discusses load balancing, which is a topic in cs.PF (Performance).
